T ‚àó = =2[n,L0, R0, T1, T2] (term depending on n,L0, R0, T1 and T2), then we know
that F [„ÄàL, n,R„Äâ] = =2[n,L,R, F [L], F [R]]. (T1 and T2 are replaced by F [L] and F [R],
respectively.)
The extracted algorithm from the proof is expressed as:
‚àÄ
n,L,R
(
